Electrameccanica Vehicles Corp. Key Developments

Electrameccanica Vehicles Corp. Announces Unaudited Earnings Results for the Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 30 17
Electrameccanica Vehicles Corp. announced unaudited earnings results for the quarter ended March 31, 2017. Net and comprehensive loss was CAD 2,189,569 or CAD 0.05 per basic and diluted share compared to CAD 1,121,083 or CAD 0.04 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash flows used in operating activities was CAD 1,854,147 compared to CAD 1,015,490 a year ago. Expenditures on property, plant and equipment were CAD 127,196 compared to CAD 15,871 a year ago. Expenditures on intellectual property were CAD 14,063.


Electrameccanica Vehicles Corp. Auditor Raises 'Going Concern' Doubt
Apr 28 17
Electrameccanica Vehicles Corp. filed its 20-F on Apr 28, 2017 for the period ending Dec 31, 2016. In this report its auditor, Dale Matheson Carr-Hilton, gave an unqualified opinion expressing doubt that the company can continue as a going concern.


Electra Meccanica Vehicles Corporation Reveals Two New Vehicles at 2017 Vancouver Auto Show
Mar 28 17
Electra Meccanica Vehicles Corporation revealed two new vehicles at the Vancouver Auto Show. The first is a vehicle called the "Tofino'. The Tofino is an all-electric, two-seat roadster representing an evolution of the classic Intermeccanica Roadster, an example of which can be seen in the EMV show stand. The other reveal vehicle on display is called the SOLO R which is a high-performance version of the SOLO electric car which debuted in September. The Tofino is equipped with a high-performance, all-electric motor with a top speed of 200 kph and a 0-100 kph in under 7 Seconds. The chassis and body are made of a lightweight aerospace-grade composite and the car is capable of up to 400 km of range on a full charge. The roadster will be available in five stunning colors including Titanium Silver, Electric Red, Raven Black, Arctic White, and Bionic Bronze with a suggested retail price starting at $50,000. Estimated deliveries will begin by 2019 and interested individuals can make a $1,000 reservation for the Tofino at the show. The SOLO R is a race-prepped performance variant of the innovative all-electric SOLO commuter vehicle, which made its world debut at Vancouver's Luxury and Supercar Weekend in September. The SOLO R has a high-performance battery system mated to performance brakes, oversized wheels and racing slicks.


