100 Mile RangeThe SOLO covers your daily commute (and plenty further) on a single charge.

137 Mph Top SpeedThink electric cars don’t have enough power? Think again: the SOLO has a top speed of 137 mph (limited to 82 mph).

0-60 in 8 SecondsThe SOLO packs a punch, rocketing from 0 to 60 in just 8 seconds.

MSRP $15,500 USDAt US$15,500, the SOLO is the best value electric vehicle on the market —even before applicable incentives.

Charge TimeWhether plugging in overnight or over lunch, dual charging allows 0-100% recharge in 3 hours on 220V, or 6 hours on 110V.

128 Nm Torque The SOLO has 82 hp and 128 Nm of torque available at the push of a pedal.

Count Your Battery Life in Days, not Miles83% of urban car trips in North America are within a 19 mile radius.

Save up to 90% EVs like the SOLO offer 3-4 times the energy efficiency of fossil fuels —it’s time for gas engines to go the way of the dodo.








