Electric Vehicles[edit]
Car components are provided from India and China, including a partnership with Zongshen Industrial Group.[1] Assembly is performed in British Columbia in New Westminster[2] and North Saanich.[3] SOLO Stores are located in Downtown Vancouver and Richmond, B.C. Canada, with plans for expansion across major cities in the USA and around the world.
SOLO[edit]




Electra Meccanica SOLO EV






The Electra Meccanica Vehicles Corp. headquarters in Vancouver, B.C. Canada


Electra Meccanica Vehicles Corp. is a Canadian car manufacturer that currently produces the SOLO, a three-wheeled, single-passenger electric vehicle. The zero-emission SOLO will is a three-wheel, battery electric vehicle marketed by Electra Meccanica as “The Smartest Commuter Car On The Planet.” The SOLO will have a 160 km (100 mile) range, a 130 km/h maximum speed and a 3-6 hour recharge time.[4] The SOLO’s 8.6 kW, 82 hp lithium-ion electric motor produces 140 ft-lbs of torque from a standstill.[5] EMV demonstrated the SOLO with a 16.1 kWh battery in September 2016, to be available in 2017.[6]
Super SOLO[edit]
Their second designed vehicle being developed is the Super SOLO, a sport-car style of the 3-wheel, single-passenger electric vehicle.
Tofino[edit]
At the Vancouver Auto conference in 2017, Electra Meccanica announced the new version Tofino that could be produced by 2019. Tofino is a 2-seated car with appearance similar to Italian 1960s versions.[7]
Origin[edit]
Electra Meccanica Vehicles Corp. was co-founded in 2015 by Henry Reisner of Intermeccanica and Jerry Kroll, former race-car champion, former CEO of CRAiLAR Technologies[8] and a 2017 Green Party MLA candidate. Kroll previously developed electric drive systems in race cars for five years at the NASA Research Park in Mountain View, California.[9] In 2017, Mark West, former President of Blenz Coffee became President of Electra Meccanica.[10]
